meanings.definition: To travel more than someone else.
meanings.sent1: She outtraveled her friend on their hike.
meanings.sent2: He outtraveled all his competitors in the race.
meanings.sent3: The tortoise outtraveled the hare in the end.
meanings.sent4: Her determination outtraveled any obstacles in her path.
meanings.sent5: The marathon runner outtraveled exhaustion to reach the finish line.

meanings.sent1: The car outtraveled the bus in reaching the destination.
meanings.sent2: Their ship outtraveled all others in the regatta.
meanings.sent3: The bicycle outtraveled the skateboard in the race.
meanings.sent4: His imagination outtraveled the limitations of reality.
meanings.sent5: The rocket outtraveled the speed of sound, breaking records.
